In life, body colourless and largely translucent (
Fig. 4
), except for melanophore patterns described above, a thin yellowish-greenish line running along body at level of neural tube; golden chromatophores forming ring around pupil, capping swimbladder chambers and connecting duct.

Distribution. The species is known only from the type locality, Jorai River in West Bengal, India (
Fig. 5
).
